#!/usr/bin/env bash
# SessionStart hook: inject the SDLC lifecycle gate in project repos.
# Emits nothing outside git repos (global-config sessions, scratch dirs).
git rev-parse --is-inside-work-tree >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 0
cat <<'EOF'
SDLC LIFECYCLE GATE (binding, from Pedro's global config):
Route coding work in this repo through the sdlc-* skills:
1. Invoke Skill(sdlc-onboard) BEFORE the first substantive task of this session.
2. Route the work: sdlc-plan (multi-step/risky) / sdlc-extend (features) / sdlc-debug (wrong behavior).
3. Invoke Skill(sdlc-validate) before declaring any nontrivial change done.
4. Invoke Skill(sdlc-handoff) before the session ends, if anything changed.
Onboard, validate, and handoff are mandatory gates even when the task looks too simple to need them — they make the project resumable by the next session.
EOF
